clarify:  "transaction.is_live" does not exist at this time.  it is specific to the condition you are checking, that the transaction has accumulated live connections.

a sample implementation would be:


@property
def is_live(self):
    return bool(self._connections)

try restoring this to __autocommit=True, then add an event handler like this, at the global level:


    import warnings
    from sqlalchemy.orm import Session
    from sqlalchemy import event

    @event.listens_for(Session, "do_orm_execute")
    def do_orm_execute(orm_execute_state):
        session = orm_execute_state.session
        if session.autocommit and not orm_execute_state.session.in_transaction():
            warnings.warn(
                "ORM session SQL execution without transaction in progress; "
                "this will 'autobegin' when autocommit=False, which is different "
                "than autocommit=True which creates an ad-hoc transaction"
            )




this will illustrate where SQL is being run on an "implicit transaction", which under autocommit is discarded immediately, and under non-autocommit creates a transaction and sticks it open.   Some or all areas where this occurs may need adjustments, either to use an ad-hoc "with session.begin()" block, or similar.

